Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State has approved a minor cabinet reshuffle, appointment and promotions with immediate effect. NAN reports that Umahi announced the changes while receiving members of the Executive Council who paid him Christmas Homage on Sunday at his home town, Uburu, in Ohaozara Local Government Area of the state. A statement by his Media Assistant, Mr Francis Nwaze, said Mrs Ann Aligwe Special Assistant (SA) on Small and Medium Enterprise (SME), has been promoted to Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on Human Capital Development and Monitoring. He said also the Special Assistant (SA) on Street Light, Mr Joseph Uguru, was recalled and posted as Special Assistant on Human Capital Development, while the Special Assistant on Ease of Doing Business, Chief Collins Agbo, is now under Ministry of Business Development. He said other reshuflement included Mr Orlando Nweze who was appointed as the Special Assistance on Capital City and Special Assistant on Internally Generated Revenue (IGR), and Mr Martin Ogwuegbu who was recalled and posted as SA on SME. He added that Dr Stephen Odoh is now Commissioner for Business Development while the Special Assistant to the Governor on Finance was promoted to Senior Special Assistant. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.